            {'myth': 'The quantum vacuum could be stable at zero energy if God willed it', 'reality': 'The uncertainty principle is not a suggestion — it is a mathematical consequence of quantum mechanics, which is confirmed to extraordinary precision. A field with exactly zero energy would violate it. No divine exemption exists in the mathematics.'},
            {'myth': 'Vacuum energy is negligible', 'reality': 'The quantum field theory prediction for vacuum energy density is 10¹²⁰ times larger than observed (the cosmological constant problem — one of the biggest unsolved issues in physics). Far from negligible, vacuum energy is the universe\'s biggest unexplained quantity.'},
