            {'title': 'The Hartle-Hawking No-Boundary Proposal', 'body': 'Stephen Hawking and James Hartle (1983) proposed the "no-boundary wave function" — a quantum description of the universe\'s origin in which time does not exist before the universe begins. Just as there is no "south of the South Pole," there is no "before the Big Bang." Time itself is a property that emerges from the quantum geometry. The universe has no beginning in time — it is a closed quantum system that simply exists. No creator is needed because there is no "before."'},
