            {'title': 'Guth\'s Inflationary Free Lunch', 'body': 'Alan Guth (1981) showed that during cosmic inflation, the positive energy of matter was created from the negative energy of the gravitational field of the inflaton. The total energy remained zero throughout. "It is often said that there is no such thing as a free lunch," Guth wrote. "But the universe itself may be the ultimate free lunch." Inflation explains the flatness, horizon, and monopole problems — and it does so while maintaining zero total energy throughout.'},
