            {'myth': 'Neuroscience has "solved" free will completely', 'reality': 'The hard philosophical question of determinism vs. indeterminism in physics is unresolved. What is settled is narrower: the specific religious model of an immaterial, uncaused chooser is not supported by any neuroscientific evidence.'},
