            {'myth': 'Belief in God is therefore a "brain defect"', 'reality': 'The opposite — these are normally functioning, adaptive cognitive systems (agency detection kept our ancestors alive) generating an unintended by-product. It is a feature, not a bug, that happens to misfire toward the supernatural.'},
