            {'myth': '"Future excavations might confirm the Bible"', 'reality': 'This is unfalsifiability. Over 150 years of systematic archaeology have been conducted at every major biblical site. The pattern of evidence is consistent: the miraculous, large-scale historical narratives are not confirmed. Adjusting the date, scale, or interpretation of each excavation to preserve the narrative is special pleading.'},
