    {'label': 'Big Bang', 'years_ago': 13_800_000_000, 'event': 'The expansion of space and time begins. Not a singularity — classical GR breaks down at the Planck scale (10⁻⁴³ s). In Hartle-Hawking quantum cosmology, time itself has no boundary here: it emerges from quantum geometry. No "before." No creator needed.', 'category': 'cosmology', 'icon': '💥'},
    {'label': 'Planck Epoch ends', 'years_ago': 13_799_999_999, 'event': 'After 10⁻⁴³ seconds the four fundamental forces were unified. Quantum gravity governed everything. This is the horizon of our knowledge — the "singularity" of old textbooks is simply where General Relativity ceases to apply.', 'category': 'cosmology', 'icon': '⚛️'},
    {'label': 'Cosmic Inflation', 'years_ago': 13_799_999_998, 'event': 'Cosmic inflation: the universe expands exponentially by a factor of 10²⁶ in 10⁻³² seconds, driven by the inflaton field. Explains why the CMB is uniform, why the universe is flat, and why total energy = 0.', 'category': 'cosmology', 'icon': '🔭'},
    {'label': 'First Atoms', 'years_ago': 13_799_620_000, 'event': 'The universe cools enough for electrons to combine with protons, forming hydrogen and helium atoms. The cosmic microwave background is released — the oldest light we can observe.', 'category': 'cosmology', 'icon': '🌡️'},
    {'label': 'First Stars', 'years_ago': 13_600_000_000, 'event': 'The first stars (Population III) ignite — enormous, hot, metal-free stellar behemoths that forge the first heavy elements.', 'category': 'astrophysics', 'icon': '⭐'},
    {'label': 'First Galaxies', 'years_ago': 13_000_000_000, 'event': 'Galaxies begin to coalesce from clouds of gas and dark matter. The universe develops its web-like large-scale structure.', 'category': 'cosmology', 'icon': '🌌'},
    {'label': 'Milky Way Forms', 'years_ago': 10_000_000_000, 'event': 'Our Milky Way galaxy assembles, incorporating earlier stellar generations whose supernovae have enriched space with heavy elements.', 'category': 'astronomy', 'icon': '🌀'},
    {'label': 'Solar System Forms', 'years_ago': 4_600_000_000, 'event': 'A cloud of gas and dust collapses to form the Sun. The remaining disk of material coalesces into planets.', 'category': 'astronomy', 'icon': '☀️'},
    {'label': 'Earth Forms', 'years_ago': 4_540_000_000, 'event': 'Earth forms through accretion of planetesimals. A Mars-sized body (Theia) collides with early Earth, ejecting material that forms the Moon.', 'category': 'astronomy', 'icon': '🌍'},
    {'label': 'First Life', 'years_ago': 3_800_000_000, 'event': 'First evidence of microbial life on Earth — prokaryotes living in ancient oceans. Chemistry becomes biology.', 'category': 'evolution', 'icon': '🧬'},
    {'label': 'Photosynthesis', 'years_ago': 3_400_000_000, 'event': 'Cyanobacteria evolve photosynthesis, beginning to release oxygen into the atmosphere.', 'category': 'evolution', 'icon': '🌿'},
    {'label': 'Great Oxidation', 'years_ago': 2_400_000_000, 'event': 'The Great Oxidation Event: oxygen accumulates in the atmosphere, transforming Earth\'s chemistry and triggering the first mass extinction.', 'category': 'evolution', 'icon': '💨'},
    {'label': 'Eukaryotes', 'years_ago': 2_000_000_000, 'event': 'First eukaryotic cells evolve — cells with a nucleus. This likely occurred when one bacterium engulfed another (endosymbiosis).', 'category': 'evolution', 'icon': '🔬'},
